# Day 03 - Insert at End (Singly Linked List)

## Definition

Insertion at the end means adding a new node after the last node of the linked list.

Example:

Before:

10 -> 20 -> 30 -> NULL

After inserting 40:

10 -> 20 -> 30 -> 40 -> NULL

---

## Algorithm

1. Create a new node.
2. If the linked list is empty, return the new node as the head.
3. Create a temporary pointer `temp` and initialize it with `head`.
4. Traverse until the last node using `while (temp.next != null)`.
5. Connect the last node to the new node using `temp.next = newNode`.
6. Return `head`.

---

## Syntax

```java
Node newNode = new Node(data);

if (head == null) {
    return newNode;
}

Node temp = head;

while (temp.next != null) {
    temp = temp.next;
}

temp.next = newNode;

return head;
```

---

