10 -> 20 -> 30 -> 40 -> NULL

---

## Time Complexity

| Operation | Complexity |
|-----------|------------|
| Insert at End | O(n) |

Reason:

Traversal is required to reach the last node.

---

## Space Complexity

| Operation | Complexity |
|-----------|------------|
| Extra Space | O(1) |

---

## Key Points

- Head does not change when inserting into a non-empty list.
- Traversal is required.
- Always stop at the last node (`temp.next == null`).
- Use a temporary pointer (`temp`) instead of moving `head`.
- If the list is empty, the new node becomes the head.

---

## Common Mistakes

### Wrong

```java
while (temp != null) {
    temp = temp.next;
}
temp.next = newNode;
```

Reason:

`temp` becomes `null`, causing a `NullPointerException`.

---

### Correct

```java
while (temp.next != null) {
    temp = temp.next;
}

temp.next = newNode;
```

---

